---
export const prerender = true;
import BlogLayout from '../../layouts/BlogLayout.astro';
import '../../styles/global.css';
---

<BlogLayout
  title="Scrabble Words from Dinosaurs — Prehistoric Terms That Score Big"
  description="Dinosaur and prehistoric words valid in Scrabble with full scoring. RAPTOR (8pts), FOSSIL (9pts), EXTINCT (16pts). Dinosaur vocabulary for competitive Scrabble players."
  keywords="scrabble dinosaur words, raptor scrabble points, fossil scrabble, extinct scrabble, prehistoric terms scrabble, dinosaur vocabulary scrabble, paleontology words scrabble"
>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"Article","headline":"Scrabble Words from Dinosaurs — Prehistoric Terms That Score Big","description":"Dinosaur and prehistoric words valid in Scrabble with full scoring. RAPTOR (8pts), FOSSIL (9pts), EXTINCT (16pts).","datePublished":"2026-06-30","author":{"@type":"Organization","name":"ScrabbleWordsFinder.com","url":"https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com"},"publisher":{"@type":"Organization","name":"ScrabbleWordsFinder.com"},"mainEntityOfPage":{"@type":"WebPage","@id":"https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com/blog/scrabble-words-from-dinosaurs"}})} />
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"FAQPage","mainEntity":[{"@type":"Question","name":"Is RAPTOR a valid Scrabble word?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes! RAPTOR scores 8 points (R=1, A=1, P=3, T=1, O=1, R=1) in Scrabble. It means a bird of prey or a predatory dinosaur. Valid in both TWL and SOWPODS dictionaries."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Can you play FOSSIL in Scrabble?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes. FOSSIL scores 9 points (F=4, O=1, S=1, S=1, I=1, L=1). The F=4 carries the scoring for this 6-letter word referring to preserved remains of ancient organisms."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Is EXTINCT valid in Scrabble?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes! EXTINCT scores 16 points (E=1, X=8, T=1, I=1, N=1, C=3, T=1) as a 7-letter bingo candidate. The X=8 makes it one of the highest-scoring 7-letter words, worth 66 points with the bingo bonus."}}]})} />
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <article class="prose prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose flex items-center gap-1"><a href="/blog/" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Blog</a><span class="mx-1">›</span><span class="text-gray-300">Word Lists</span></nav>
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Scrabble Words from Dinosaurs — Prehistoric Terms That Score Big</h1>
      <div class="not-prose mb-8 flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400"><time datetime="2026-06-30">June 30, 2026</time><span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span><span>5 min read</span><span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span><a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🔤</span> Word Finder</a></div>
      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-300 mb-8">Dinosaurs may be extinct, but their vocabulary is alive and thriving in Scrabble. Prehistoric terminology features X tiles, F tiles, and useful letter combinations that make these ancient words powerful tools for modern gameplay.</p>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">16 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">EXTINCT</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">9 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">FOSSIL</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">8 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">RAPTOR</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">14 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">EPOCH</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Top-Scoring Dinosaur Words</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-8 p-6 rounded-2xl border-2 border-amber-500/50 bg-gradient-to-r from-amber-950/30 to-yellow-950/20 relative overflow-hidden">
        <div class="absolute top-3 right-4 text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-amber-500/70">👑 Top Scorer</div>
        <p class="text-2xl font-black text-white tracking-wider mb-2">EXTINCT — 16 Points</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-amber-300 font-semibold mb-3">E=1, X=8, T=1, I=1, N=1, C=3, T=1 · 7 letters · Bingo candidate</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">No longer existing as a species. EXTINCT is a 7-letter bingo candidate scoring 16 base points. With X=8 and C=3, it earns 66 points total with the 50-point bingo bonus. A devastating play.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10"><p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🦴 FOSSIL</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">9 pts · F=4, O=1, S=1, S=1, I=1, L=1 · Preserved remains</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10"><p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🦖 RAPTOR</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">8 pts · R=1, A=1, P=3, T=1, O=1, R=1 · Predatory dinosaur</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-cyan-500/30 bg-cyan-950/10"><p class="text-cyan-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">⏳ EPOCH</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">14 pts · E=1, P=3, O=1, C=3, H=4 · Period of time</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-cyan-500/30 bg-cyan-950/10"><p class="text-cyan-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🪨 PETRIFY</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">15 pts · P=3, E=1, T=1, R=1, I=1, F=4, Y=4 · Turn to stone</p></div>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Paleontology Vocabulary</h2>
      <p>Prehistoric science terminology provides a range of scoring options from accessible tiles:</p>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-3">
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">BONES</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">7pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">CLAW</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">9pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">FANG</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">8pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">PREY</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">9pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">SCALE</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">7pts</span></span>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Strategy for Dinosaur Words</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">EXTINCT is your X-tile bingo:</span> At 7 letters with X=8, EXTINCT (16pts + 50 bonus = 66pts) is one of the most powerful bingos containing X. Keep E, T, I, N, C, T when you hold X.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">PETRIFY combines F and Y:</span> F=4 and Y=4 together in PETRIFY (15pts) give you 8 points from just two tiles. Add P=3 and it's a strong 7-letter play worth 65 points with bingo.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">FOSSIL uses the F tile reliably:</span> F=4 is often hard to play well. FOSSIL (9pts) uses it with common tiles (O, S, S, I, L) — a solid dump play that clears difficult letters.</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">💡 Key Insight</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">Dinosaur words are <span class="text-white font-medium">X-tile and F-tile specialists</span>. EXTINCT delivers X=8 in a bingo, FOSSIL and PETRIFY use F=4 effectively, and EPOCH pairs P+C+H for 10 points from three tiles. When you draw X or F, think prehistoric — this vocabulary handles them naturally.</p>
      </div>
      <aside class="border-t border-gray-800 mt-12 pt-8 not-prose">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Related Articles</h3>
        <div class="grid gap-3">
          <a href="/blog/scrabble-words-from-geology/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Words from Geology</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/scrabble-words-from-science/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Words from Science</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/scrabble-nature-words/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Nature Words</span></a>
        </div>
      </aside>
      <div class="not-prose mt-10 p-5 bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-900/20 to-cyan-900/20 border border-blue-800 rounded-xl shadow-sm">
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4 flex-wrap">
          <p class="text-sm text-blue-300 font-medium">🔤 Find every valid prehistoric word instantly — free Scrabble solver, no sign-up</p>
          <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg bg-blue-600 hover:bg-blue-700 text-white text-sm font-semibold transition-colors shadow-sm">Open Word Finder →</a>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose mt-8 text-center"><a href="/blog/" class="text-sm text-gray-400 hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Back to all articles</a></div>
    </article>
  </div>
</BlogLayout>
